The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 12 April is 268,978 (31,001.3 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 07 April, there were 4,342 new confirmed cases (500.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 31 March, there were 7,196 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 40% (2,854 fewer cases).
